The paper introduces two Python frameworks for training neural networks on large datasets, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on the development of tools for training complex neural network models. The second most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper specifically deals with neural networks. The third most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as deep learning has been widely used in computer vision applications. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as deep learning is a subfield of AI. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper mentions the use of CUDA-support for parallel computing.
